Ultrasonic evaluation of the upper abdomen in cystic fibrosis. Abdominal sonography should compulsory be used in patients with cystic fibrosis (CF). It is not difficult to detect early morphologic changes at liver, gall-bladder, pancreas, spleen, and vessels by ultrasound. As a non-invasive method sonography is a very useful tool for a comprehensive special care of outpatients with CF.